items.about:
The world is handing the keys of a Ferrari to every health marketing team on the planet. That Ferrari is Generative AI. It allows brands to move at 200mph. But without a seatbelt (trustworthy compliance) that speed creates a massive legal risk.

We are building that seatbelt.

My obsession with this problem started 15 years ago on the floor of Procter & Gamble, where I experience firsthand how "Legal" was the bottleneck to growth.

I spent the next decade building the skillset to solve it: 

At Palantir: I learned how to deploy data infrastructure into complex, critical environments.
At Citi: I managed a $2.8B P&L and navigated the regulatory chaos of Brexit as Chief of Staff to the UK CEO.
At Wheely: I led operations during "wartime," relocating 23% of our workforce during the onset of the Russia-Ukraine war while reaching profitability.

Now, I am combining that operational experience with the medical knowledge of my co-founder (Dr. Leonie Bode) to solve one of the biggest problems in the $600B Longevity Economy.

We are the department of "Yes!" We utilise proprietary AI to validate and localise their claims instantly, turning compliance from a bottleneck into a growth engine.

3x Scale-Up Operator turned Founder. Competitive CrossFit Athlete. On a mission to bring truth to health commerce.
items.tagline: Co-Founder at Stealth (HealthTech) | Ex-Palantir, Wheely, Citi ($2.8 B P&L)
items.Name: Karina Valencia

items.about:
Alfonso Iovieno is an experienced senior executive with 18 years of leadership in e-Commerce and Digital Payments, most recently shaping innovative product strategies for global leaders in financial services. Known for aligning product innovation with business goals and customer needs, Alfonso combines strategic vision with a people-first leadership philosophy built on trust, empowerment, and accountability. 

Throughout his career, Alfonso has held key roles at industry giants including Vodafone, VISA, J.P. Morgan Chase, and Citigroup, where he built and managed product portfolios that redefined customer experiences across North America, LATAM, and EMEA. His expertise spans product lifecycle management, business modeling, pricing, digital idenity authentication, and AI-driven analytics, making him a proven problem-solver who thrives at the intersection of technology and financial services.

In parallel, Alfonso has served as Founder & Strategic Advisor, driving initiatives at the edge of innovation. He has advised an Agentic AI startup building virtual shopping assistants for e-commerce, designed an Innovation Lab strategy to help Corporate Development teams commercialize emerging tech, and built the strategy, team, and funding roadmap for a compliance and cybersecurity startup focused on data strategy and GenAI integration. Across these ventures, he has guided founders from concept to go-to-market, delivering sustainable growth and long-term value.

Beyond his corporate roles, Alfonso is an advocate for cross-cultural collaboration and knowledge-sharing within the digital ecosystem. He has actively engaged in mentoring and coaching emerging leaders, while also contributing to industry forums and innovation roundtables. Passionate about continuous learning and global connectivity, he values diversity, creativity, and the power of technology to enhance human experiences.

With dual citizenship (US and EU) and eligibility for a UK visa, Alfonso is well-positioned to contribute to global organizations at the forefront of digital innovation.

items.description: Raspberry AI is a leading provider of generative AI design software for fashion brands and retailers. The platform enables companies to rapidly understand consumer demand and create unique designs in minutes, significantly improving speed-to-market and reducing sample costs. With features like photorealistic rendering, technical drawings, and lifestyle photography, Raspberry AI helps brands streamline their design processes and enhance collaboration. The company has gained traction with significant savings on sample costs and time, positioning itself as a key player in the fashion tech industry.
